main event: U.S. Navy employees sighted high-speed, disc-shaped objects over San Diego, California on 17 December 1952.
interesting points: The objects were described as cigar-shaped or disc-like and changed shape as they traveled., The speed of the objects varied from that of conventional jet aircraft to around 2000 miles per hour., Observations were made by qualified personnel including electronic scientists from the Navy., The sighting occurred between 1715 and 1825 hours., Personnel agreed the objects were definitely not conventional aircraft.
witness description: employees of the U.S. Navy Electronics Laboratory
